Description:
Modern Convenience
Moments to Batman station and Upfield Bike Path, this two-bedroom, two-bathroom apartment is modern and convenient. Oversized East facing windows fill the spacious living area soaked with natural light, sliding glass doors out to your own private balcony. The property is well serviced by modern main and ensuite bathroom plus a smart kitchen boasting glass splashbacks, stone counters and modern appliances. Other features include split system air conditioning, European style laundry, secure carport, storage cage, video intercom and BIRs. Convenience, modern style and easy lifestyle assure investor, downsizer and starter appeal. Inspections are a must.

Description:
Large 3 bedroom home filled with natural light
Living so close to the CBD and centrally located within metres of Nicholson Street Tram, Bell Street Bus and a leisurely stroll to Central Coburg makes this large home the logical choice. Whether you are looking for a large living option or addition to your rental portfolio this home is it.

Description:
Impressive Space with Light and Location
One of only four in a well-maintained block, this two-storey townhouse is a must-see for home buyers and investors alike with its generous dimensions, immaculate presentation and prized location within the Strathmore Secondary College zone. Easy-living excellence, the home's light-filled interior comprises three spacious upstairs bedrooms (two with BIRs, master with WIR), two-way central bathroom as well as separate WCs on each level. Add to this a sizeable front lounge leading through to the open dining area and adjoining kitchen. Other highlights include heating and cooling, full-size laundry and under-stair storeroom. Step outside to discover a wide north-facing courtyard and rear access into the remote-control garage. Walking distance to Reynard Street buses and Melville Road trams, local cafes and popular primary schools, it's also close to Coburg Station and renowned shopping precinct along with easy access to Citylink. Terrific low-maintenance living or investing! Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Irresistible family space & style in beautiful environs
There's a sensational inner-city family feel about this outstanding 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom Edwardian that's superbly set amidst beautiful gardens on surprisingly spacious allotment. Renovated and extended to accommodate an active family that loves their space, the wide single-level interior is brilliantly laid out capturing streams of north light as it delights with a carefully considered combination of classical and contemporary style. The heart of the home is a huge modern kitchen replete with Smeg/Bosch appliances and stone benchtops. Towards the front, the main bedroom features a bank of BIRs and stunning ensuite while at the rear is a large living and dining room spilling out to a secluded, leafy garden with entertainment patio and studio/workshop. Integrating a north-facing alfresco deck, highlights of this extra special home include designer bathroom with freestanding bath and Laufen/SaphirKeramik vanity, separate laundry, attic storage, gas heating, reverse-cycle air-conditioning, security alarm, exquisite lighting, polished floorboards, stained glass, heated towel racks, garden irrigation and carport. Desirably located on a quiet street near Merri Creek parkland and trails, Sydney Road shops and restaurants, schools, trams and train station.

Stylish Spaces, Lifestyle Ease
Brightly refurbished interiors and a generous free-flowing design make this three bedroom townhouse a standout for those who love low-maintenance living without sacrificing on space. Flooded in natural light courtesy of a stylish courtyard light well, expansive lounge with bay window and informal living flank a quality appointed island kitchen. Description:
OCCUPY, INVEST OR DEVELOP!
In one of Coburg best pockets lies this charming solid brick home boasting plenty of potential. Within walking distance to Gilmour Park, Pooley Reserve, the vibrant Holmes Street, Nicholson Street and Sydney Road including its cafes, restaurants and public transport on offer.
This grand family home has so much on offer bathed in natural light, you will be surprised what you will find walking through the front door. The top level features an open plan well-equipped kitchen/dining area with a walk-in pantry adjoining onto the large living area with a Romeo balcony. Three generous size bedrooms, the master bedroom includes your own private ensuite, while one of the other bedrooms feature a built-in wardrobe, all serviced by the central bathroom with a separate walk in pantry for extra storage space.
Heading downstairs is where the property really gets interesting, offering a self-contained two- bedroom, one bathroom, kitchen and living area perfect for the astute investor looking for a dual income property. Also, for those car enthusiasts a four-car garage with a cellar storage, a kitchenette and a bathroom with laundry facilities.
Highly sought-after North facing backyard with a large variety of Fruit trees with a workshop and shed or simply clear the space and create your own outdoor oasis. Situated on a generous allotment of 631m2 approx block with development potential (STCA).

Description:
Exceptional Living Areas & Six Bedrooms!
This is a rare find and ideal for a large family looking for a home that offers all the modern comforts and lifestyle living in a central location. Designed to entertain in style with three living zones, a fully appointed quality kitchen, two bathrooms, heating and cooling. Perfectly positioned and within walking distance to the Coburg Lake Reserve, schools, transport, playgrounds and Sydney Road Shopping Precinct.
You won't be disappointed!
PROPERTY SPECIFICATIONS:
- BUILT: In 2001 approximately and a one owner home.
- CONSTRUCTION: Brick veneer home under a concrete tiled roof.
- LAND AREA: 435m2 approximately.
- BUILDING: Building internal area is 20 squares approximately.
- BEDROOMS: Five spacious bedrooms with carpeted flooring all with sliding mirrored built
in robes,
- STUDY: Double entry with carpeted flooring and built in cupboard.
- KITCHEN: A vinyl wrap white kitchen with breakfast bench, pantry and an abundance of
cupboard and bench space.
Also includes a stainless steel 5 burner gas hot plate, wall oven/microwave,
dishwasher and rangehood.
- MEALS: East facing, tiled flooring with sliding door access to the rear yard.
- LOUNGE/DINING: Tiled formal lounge and dining room with bay window,
- FAMILY ROOM: East facing, tiled flooring and overlooking the rear yard.
- BATHROOM: Tiled with a corner bath, corner shower and a single vanity.
- ENSUITE: Tiled with a corner spa bath, corner shower, single vanity and toilet.
- POWDER ROOM: Toilet and single vanity.
- LAUNDRY: Spacious with built in cupboard and single trough. .
- OUTDOORS: Extensive pattern paved concrete perfect for entertaining and low maintenance
backyard facing north/east.
- PARKING: Rear access via right of way to a single carport and off street parking.
- FEATURES: Gas ducted heating, two split system air-conditioners, low voltage downlights
and window coverings.
- POTENTIAL RENTAL RETURN: $700 - $770 p/w (approx.)
LOCATION BENEFITS:
- Located within close distance to Sydney Road Shopping Precinct, parks and local schools
- Walking distance multiple transport service with only 200m to the Tram line on Sydney Road
and 450m to the Batman Train Station and 1.2km to the Coburg Train Station.
- Coburg is located 9km's north of the CBD with terrific City Link and Melbourne Airport
access.
One not to be missed!
Insights: 11 Deans Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019.

Description:
UNDER OFFER
Within walking distance of everything cosmopolitan Coburg has on offer, this captivating three bedroom federation home also boasts a modern studio with open plan living/kitchen/meals and separate home office/storeroom. Behind a charming façade, featuring wraparound verandah, French doors and original windows, a classic layout features soaring ceilings, fretwork, picture rails, timber mantel and polished Baltic pine floorboards throughout formal hallway, lounge and beautifully presented bedrooms. Towards the rear finds an updated timber kitchen, with gas stove, and light filled dining area opening to an undercover alfresco entertaining zone and backyard. Enhanced with period-inspired bathroom, BIR, open fireplace/heating/cooling, alarm and side driveway providing coveted off street parking. Enjoy easy access to Coburg Market, shops, cafés, restaurants, schools, Coburg Lake and public transport.

Description:
Exceptionally Spacious Top-Floor Apartment
Moments from Sydney Roads array of shops, cafes and restaurants, this bright and exceptionally spacious (64.5sqm) top floor one-bedroom apartment is both a rare opportunity and a refreshing take on apartment living, making it a snazzy and savvy investment for both your lifestyle and property future.
Flipping the stereotypical boxy apartment bedroom on its head, the master bedroom here is vast, with room for a queen-size bed and your very own private relaxation nook think a couch and/or a desk plus heating, a built-in robe and beautiful views, offering a touch of hotel chic to your home. Across the hall, you'll find the bathroom, featuring bathtub.
A modern kitchen with spacious benchtops, stainless steel appliances (including dishwasher) and exceptional storage options looks out towards a sizeable light and airy open-plan lounge and dining area, before spilling out onto an expansive balcony (approx 6.7sqm) that offers the kind of exclusive unencumbered top-floor views people visit sky-high bars and fancy hotels to witness the perfect spot for enjoying a morning cuppa as the sun rises and afternoons feasting with family and friends.
Other coveted features include European laundry, separate toilet, remote control entry to secure basement car space, intercom and NBN-ready connection.
Within walking distance of Merri Creek and its walking trails, Coburg Farmers Market, local leisure centres, trams and busses, Coburg Train Station, this apartment is an opportunity not to be missed.
**Please Note: To gain entry at inspections, please buzz apartment number at the door.**
Insights: 404a/41-43 Stockade Avenue, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 26 other 1 bedroom unit in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Design Excellence and Cutting-Edge Style
With its own street frontage this townhouse delivers a lifestyle of absolute quality and class with its spacious interior, long list of luxuries and prime location just north of Brunswick's border. Beyond the striking facade, discover a stunning interior showcasing three generous bedrooms (all with robes) and two deluxe bathrooms - each with concealed cisterns and floor-to-ceiling tiles. Add to this a stylish kitchen with Franke double sink and Miele appliances, expansive and light-filled open living/dining area with stacker doors revealing a wide terrace complete with city skyline views. Other features include heating and cooling, soft-close drawers/cupboards and stone benchtops throughout, hardwood floors, alarm and video intercom, ducted vacuum, double-glazed windows and doors, solar/gas hot water, plus rear courtyard, internally-accessed garage and additional driveway parking space. Close to a range of lifestyle attractions including Melville Road trams and Moreland Station, local parks, popular primary schools and vibrant shopping precincts, as well as easy access to Citylink. Fully-optioned modern living!

Description:
CALIFORNIAN BUNGALOW IN TIGHTLY HELD TREE-LINED LOCATION
This double fronted Californian Bungalow is situated in blue ribbon pocket of trendy Coburg and is awaiting its next chapter.
This family home has been in the same family for over 50 years, and the next family can add their own personal touch with a simple renovation to enhance its period features and take advantage of its large backyard, and extend the home, or retain as a great investment.
A flexible floor plan of 3 bedrooms or 2 and formal lounge, functional bathroom, open lounge/meals area and kitchen looking out to large rear yard sunny backyard, and carport access at the front for off street parking complete the package.
Other features include ducted heating throughout, evaporative cooling, ornate ceilings and baltic pine floors under carpets, large external laundry, plus a north westerly backyard with large undercover pergola/ carport, large storage shed/ potential garage or studio, gate access to ROW with potential to put large double garage door for access for tradies, caravan, boat or trailer.
Walking distance to lifestyle attractions including popular primary schools (St Fidelis and Coburg West), local parks and public transport options, it's also close to Sydney Road cafes, restaurants and Coburg's renowned shopping precinct.
Make this your next special home or great blue investment with potential to extend up or out, and reap the rewards of solid capital growth and current rental return of $27,636 per annum.
This won't last long!

Description:
The Ideal Investment Approach
An edge-of-the-park position that embodies relaxed living readily complements this stylish, modern apartment. The attraction of its investment prospects are enhanced by sizeable shaded courtyard garden that brings a breath of fresh air inwards and contributes markedly to the appeal of open living zone and stone/stainless-steel kitchen. The large bedroom is tidily tucked away to the rear with ensuite and walk-too-wall robes, accompanied by adjacent European laundry and powder room. Includes air conditioning, heating, secure entry, storage cage and a secure car space. With evident first-home buyer or investment appeal offering close proximity to the pleasures of Sydney Rd, trams and trains nearby.

Description:
Period Charm Meets Modern Living
Everything that's wonderful about modern living and lifestyle location is right here. Boasting an abundance of natural light and polished floorboards throughout, this spectacular home will leave you wanting more. From high ceilings with rosettes and deep-dish cornices this gorgeous home screams period delight!
Walking into the property you are greeted with an exquisite double fronted façade with a well-maintained garden and more than enough space for you to do as you wish. Three generous size bedrooms all featuring ornamental fireplaces, the master bedroom comes with a walk-in wardrobe and your own private ensuite, while the two other bedrooms include built in wardrobes. Serviced by a central bathroom complete with a bathtub and a separate shower.
Open plan kitchen/dining and living area featuring a 60mm stone bench top, stainless steel appliances, a butler's pantry and separate laundry with an abundance of bench and cupboard space. Flowing out to the North-facing alfresco area via the French glass sliding doors, overlooking the immaculate rear yard with a beautiful central Palm tree, providing the perfect entertaining area for family and friends all year round.
Completing this superb haven is ducted heating, split system air conditioning and a secret wine cellar, perfect for storing your fine wine's. Perfectly positioned in the Coburg Senior High School zone and just a short stroll to Coburg Train Station, the vibrant Sydney Road with all its shops, cafes and restaurants on offer.
This is a fantastic opportunity and all yours for the taking!
Insights: 21 Vincent Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Potential Packed Entry To A Premier Locale
Boasting a premier Coburg address this single level one bedroom villa unit, is remarkable in its generous proportions, and perfectly fulfils the first home owner or investment wish list. Privately positioned in a boutique block of only five, this spacious unit puts you at the heart of a lifestyle locale where cosmopolitan Sydney Road, trams, Moreland Station and Merri Creek parklands are all walking distance, and a short tram trip finds you at the CBD. Be inspired to add contemporary appeal with an update that will showcase this property's generous lounge and adjoining kitchen with meals that opens to a sizeable courtyard offering ample space in which to relax and entertain. The double bedroom with built-in robe is serviced by a large bathroom incorporating laundry facilities, while a gas heater and single car space complete this home. Handy to local cafes, shopping, parks and the Upfield Bike Path this potential packed home is positioned to please and sure to inspire.

Description:
Californian bungalow, garden sanctuary.
Nestled in beautifully landscaped gardens, this captivating three bedroom plus study Californian bungalow offers an idyllic sanctuary whilst within walking distance of cafés, schools and city transport. Preceded by leadlight entry, charming hallway and renovated accommodation, are expansive open plan living/dining/kitchen zones where a magnificent garden outlook draws you onto an undercover alfresco deck designed for seamless indoor/outdoor entertaining. Quality appliances, modern counter tops/island bench and abundant cabinetry complement a large, light filled kitchen zone. Features three spacious bedrooms/BIRS, central bathroom, polished floorboards, high ceilings, ducted heating, split-system air conditioner, ceiling fans, solar electricity, underfloor insulation, off street parking and potential rear ROW access. On land, approximately 572sqm, close to Sydney Road shops, markets, scenic Coburg Lake and Merri Creek bike paths.

Description:
Auction This Saturday 26th of October at 2.30pm
Renovated and radiant, this elegant three bedroom plus studio Californian bungalow presents stylish accommodation in a convenient locale. Beyond the classic leadlight window façade, a hallway lined with timber floorboards accesses three spacious bedrooms and a welcoming lounge boasting a traditional open fireplace. The modern kitchen/meals is fully appointed with stainless steel appliances and extends via stacker servery window and doors to a vast all-weather alfresco deck overlooking tranquil landscaped gardens. The studio alternatively repurposes as a comfortable fourth bedroom (split system air conditioner) while a pristine laundry, bathroom and second toilet complete sparkling amenities. Ducted heating, evaporative air conditioning and off street parking round out an exciting offering. Centrally placed with schools, parks, the Merri Creek Trail and tram at your fingertips, families, professionals and investors will be suitably impressed.
